 Educational Background



 


New York University - Leonard N. Stern School of Business

                  Since its inception in 1900, New York University Stern School of Business has been in and of New York City.

Founded as the School of Commerce, Finance, and Accounting, the School initially offered training to students for careers in commerce in the burgeoning financial markets of New York City. 

Today, located in the heart of Greenwich Village with a campus in Westchester, Stern is one of the nation’s premier management education schools and research centers with a broad portfolio of academic programs at the graduate and undergraduate levels. With its global partnerships and engagement in NYU’s global network university, today NYU Stern is not only in and of the city, but also in and of the world.                




 


University of Bristol

                  The University of Bristol is a red brick research university that offers a range of educational courses and services. 


The university is organized into six academic facilities: Faculty of Arts, Faculty of Engineering, Faculty of Medical and Veterinary Sciences, Faculty of Science, Faculty of Medicine and Dentistry, and Faculty of Social Sciences and Law. These faculties together award a range of academic degrees spanning bachelor's and master's degrees as well as junior doctorates and higher doctorates.


University of Bristol was established in 1876 and is based in Bristol, United Kingdom.                





